instructor.last.name: Bond
instructor.first.name: Marjorie
section.anomalies: Section 1 is Elementary Statistics which has no math pre-req. and is required for Sociology majors and recommended for Psychology majors.  Section 2 is Statistics for the Life Sciences which has "college level math ability" pre-req.  This course is taken by pre-Med; Bio-Chemistry majors; Biology majors; Environmental Science majors; an occasional Bio-Psychology major; and math majors (rare).
textbook.used: Section 1: Staistics in Practice Moore/Notz/Fling....; Section 2: Statistics for the Sciences Baldi & Moore
student.type: First-year students/sophomores wanting to develop background necessary for their intended specialization
primary.new.content.obtainment: Reading Assignment in "theory." I don't believe that most achieve this.  Students who don't like to read can use the videos that are associated with the textbook.
skills.practice_other: Learning Curve through on-line activities; Reading journal articles.
accountability.assignments_other: Working in groups to present on the board.
incentive.pre: Told extra credit, but one point was placed on the exam average.
incentive.post: Students could have taken test during last week of classes as well..... Students were told that if they took the post-test that they would receive one point on the Other category.
